# Internal docs (extraction reference, not public — kept as a guard even if /docs/ is absent).
# Narrow exceptions: bloat and bench baselines are checked in so the size-gate
# CI job has something to diff regressions against. The `/docs/*` form
# (rather than `/docs/`) is required because `gitignore(5)` does not honor
# `!` re-inclusions inside an excluded directory.
/docs/*
!/docs/bloat-baseline-*.txt
!/docs/bench-baseline-*.txt
NOTES.md
TODO.md
ARCHITECTURE.md
COMPETITIVE_ANALYSIS.md
UX_IMPROVEMENTS.md
SKILLS_SECURITY.md
GETTING_STARTED.md
kernex-agent.md

